%N A397732 a(n) is the number of distinct triples of triangles chosen from n^2 unit triangles of a triangular grid up to rotation such that no two triangles share a common point.
%C A397732 Triples containing pairs of triangles denoted by their centers coupled (h,k) with any of the following are removed to avoid triangles with common points: (h+1,k-2), (h+1,k+1), (h-2,k+1), (h-2,k-2), (h,k-3), (h+3,k-3), (h+4,k-2), (h+3,k), (h,k+3), (h-2,k+4), (h-3,k+3), (h-3,k).
%H A397732 Sean A. Irvine, <a href="/A397732/b397732.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..85</a>
%H A397732 Janaka Rodrigo, <a href="/A397732/a397732.txt">Python code</a>
%H A397732 Janaka Rodrigo, <a href="/A397732/a397732.pdf">Illustration for n = 4</a>
%F A397732 Conjectured g.f.: 2*x^3 * (1+9*x+39*x^2+28*x^3+3*x^4-21*x^5-5*x^6+6*x^7) / ((1+x+x^2) * (1-x)^7). - _Sean A. Irvine_, Jul 14 2026
%e A397732 n = 3 has two distinct triples of triangles: {(1,1),(1,7),(5,2)}, {(1,1),(1,7),(7,1)}. Therefore a(3) = 2.
